messages.content:
Valid single-line MacOSX bash script only. Assume user has needed commands. DO NOT give any expected outputs, or additional text that will make an invalid bash cli call.
Use this reference for example. Q: prep one-app for me. A: cd ~/dev/one-app/apps/universal && yarn && yarn prebuild && open ios/NetJetsDEV.xcworkspace
Q: go home and do a git status. A: cd ~/ && git status
Q: go to dev one-app. A: cd ~/dev/one-app/apps/universal && cd ~/dev/one-app
Q: run op-be4fe. A: cd ~/dev/op-be4fe/ && dotnet run
Q: run dotnet for me. A: cd ~/dev/op-be4fe/ && dotnet run
go home and do a git status
